  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Text Updated as of May 28, 2005: IFC, in 2005, committed multiple investments totaling $15 million in the Ramky Group (Group) which consisted of investments in Ramky Enviro Engineers Limited (REEL), a company handling the Groups waste management business, to part-finance the establishment of a number of waste management facilities and also investments in Ramky Infrastructure Limited (RIL), the engineering, procurement and construction (EPC) arm of the Group for various infrastructure sectors. Subsequently, the committed investment in REEL was cancelled and IFC proceeded with only a part of the committed investment in RIL ($3 million), though the nature of this investment in RIL has also been significantly modified.</narrative>
  </description>
